IslandWay
Montreal, Canada83 contributions
5.0 of 5 bubbles
Halong Bay cruise with Eco Friendly Vietnam
Dec 2010
My wife and I as well as our friends (family of 4) spent 3 days 2 nights with Eco Friendly Vietnam this Christmas. Eco Friendly Vietnam only does private tours. The boat was perfect for us with 2 rooms with double beds and 1 room with 2 single beds for the kids.

The tour is not actually in Halong Bay but in Bai Tu Long bay (correct me if I am wrong). Instead of driving all the way to Halong city we were driven to Haiphong. From there were take a hydrofoil to Cat Ba island where the tour starts.
They picked up our friends at their hotels at 6:15 and then came to ours for 6:30. Since the driver does not speak english there is an english speaking rep when they pick you up in Hanoi. She explained everything to us, gave us our hydrofoil ticket and that was it.
We took the hyrofoil from Haiphong to Cat Ba. We were then greeted in Cat Ba by Lieu (I had been in contact with him to organise this trip) and a mini van with driver. We drove 10 mins to another port on another side of the island and there our junk was.
On our first day we cruised in the bay, stopped to pick up some kayaks and went to a nice bay for lunch.
We then cruised again up to the spot where we stopped to do some kayaking. There were no other tourists around and this was our most enjoyable kayak excursion.
This day we also got to swim a little, cruise some more and find a nice secluded bay for diner and the night.
The second day was similar. We went kayaking again but this time there were other tourist boat and we were never alone. I think we were then in Halong Bay and that would explain the number of boats. However our guide told us it was usually never that crowded.I guess this is because the spot is renowned for it's very long caves.
We went swimming again but this time it was at a beach. Some of us kayaked there while my wife swam. This little secluded beach was so beautiful.
We then went to visit a fish farm and after that our captain found us a nice little bay to spend the evening and the night.
The third day was really interresting and it was also sunny with a clear sky. We were very lucky as this does not happen often during the winter. So this day, we went to Monkey island. Seeing the monkeys is an experience itself but we also got to hike up the top of the hill where the view is simply amazing. See the first video, this is the view from the top of the island.
After Monkey island, we went swimming again. We cruised back toward Cat Ba, had lunch in a nice little bay (again!) and this was the end of the trip. We were lucky because the boat was not picking up any other tourist that day, so we were able to stay a good 2-3 hours more on board! This is a nice extra for sure!
Other comments:
For the 6 of us, there were 3 staff on the boat: the captain, the cook and the guide. The captain and the cook spoke little english but they were nice people. All were great guys.
We ate a lot of fish and seafood. There was always plenty enough for all of us and I think we were never able to finish everything they gave us.
We were spending most of the time on the top of the boat where there were 4 sun loungers.
We also booked our Hanoi hotel with Eco Friendly Vietnam. We stayed at the Hanoi Paradise Hotel 2 and it was a good value 3* hotel with perfect location.
Bring warm cloths, it can get cold at night in the winter. However, the water was always warm!
Written March 22, 2011
topps82
Manchester, UK1 contribution
HALONG BAY BOAT TOUR - SAPPHIRE SAIL - LOST PASSPORT
Feb 2011
We booked at 2 day 1 night trip to Halong bay through our hotel,on their recommendation. It cost $160 for two people, supposedly a luxury tour ( although we later dicovered that some people had paid as little as $50 per person for the same trip ) The tour guide collected us from the hotel and collected everyones passports in order to get the tickets etc.. something that were very reluctant to do. He told us he would return the passport when we handed the room key in the following morning. When we did this my passport was MISSING! They hadn't a clue where it was. We tried to phone the police and the captain of the boat would not speak to them. It was a real battle because the supposedly 'english speaking tour guide' had very poor english and couldn't understand us. We finally got a police report when we got onto land. It took us 3 days for me to get an emergency passport - as it was the weekend. I then had to wait 3 days for a new Vietnam visa to leave the country. The company offered us no money back for the trip and we had to fight to get the money back for the passport and the visa. We are very disappointed with standard of service ( as many other customers were as well) and the way we were treated - a complete lack of empathy and compassion, we would not recommend this boat to anyone. Please be careful when booking a tour to Halong bay and maybe try and give a copy of your passport instead. We have learnt a very harsh lesson and it has been a very unpleasant experience.
