Melbourne, Australia222 contributions
Dragon's Pearl cruise, IndoChina Junk - Beyond Expectation
We recently chartered the Dragon's Pearl junk from Indochina junk company. There were 11 cabins in the junk for the 13 of us. Room decor was nice, and the service excellent. Food was tasty and beautifully presented. Bathroom was spotless, and bed linens clean and crisp. Two bottles of water was provided per room. Apart from that, one had to pay to get any drink.
Many activities were provided and included in the cost of the cruise. Eg, kayaking, fishing, morning visit to a floating fishing village, ride on a sampan in beautiful bay, and exploring a cave. Our guide was good and provided informative commentary of the area.
I would highly recommend this junk to others
